          <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">What's the difference between perfume oil and attar?<span class="mi" aria-hidden="true">add</span></summary><div class="faq-a">Both are alcohol-free oils. Attar traditionally refers to natural distillations — often oud, rose or musk — while perfume oils can also be modern blended compositions. Both wear close to the skin and last for hours.</div></details>
          <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">Which category lasts longest in UAE heat?<span class="mi" aria-hidden="true">add</span></summary><div class="faq-a">Arabic perfumes, oud-based fragrances and attars perform exceptionally in warm climates thanks to rich, heavy base notes. Look for our 8–12 hour longevity tags, or ask the AI concierge.</div></details>
          <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">Are inspired perfumes authentic?<span class="mi" aria-hidden="true">add</span></summary><div class="faq-a">Our inspired lines are original compositions that echo the character of iconic scents — always clearly labelled as inspired-by, never sold as the genuine designer original. Our designer and Arabic-house resale is 100% authentic, verified-sourced stock.</div></details>
          <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">Do you offer Cash on Delivery across all categories?<span class="mi" aria-hidden="true">add</span></summary><div class="faq-a">Yes — Cash on Delivery is available across all seven Emirates, alongside Tabby & Tamara interest-free instalments, Apple Pay, Google Pay and cards.</div></details>
